00:00:08.390 --> 00:00:11.030
JACK: Very, very special
guest today with us here

00:00:11.030 --> 00:00:15.060
on Main Campus in
building 43 at Google.

00:00:15.060 --> 00:00:18.290
This individual who's going
to speak with us today

00:00:18.290 --> 00:00:20.480
is somebody who has
revolutionized medicine

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:24.440
and health care, both
here in the US and abroad,

00:00:24.440 --> 00:00:26.255
with a 35-year career.

00:00:26.255 --> 00:00:28.577
And we'll hear very soon
about the early part

00:00:28.577 --> 00:00:30.160
of his career, where
he really started

00:00:30.160 --> 00:00:32.009
on a very different track--

00:00:32.009 --> 00:00:34.970
a track that took him
to a lot of new ideas

00:00:34.970 --> 00:00:37.730
that have brought us
to a lot of revolutions

00:00:37.730 --> 00:00:41.930
across cardiac care,
diabetes, and now Alzheimer's

00:00:41.930 --> 00:00:44.870
and other diseases as well.

00:00:44.870 --> 00:00:47.600
Our guest today has six
books, all best sellers

00:00:47.600 --> 00:00:49.820
on "The New York Times"
Best Sellers list.

00:00:49.820 --> 00:00:52.790
Our guest today graduated from
the Baylor College of Medicine

00:00:52.790 --> 00:00:56.660
