00:34:54.060 --> 00:34:54.929
of people who have gone through.

00:34:54.929 --> 00:34:56.845
But you're right, the
traditional Indian diet,

00:34:56.845 --> 00:34:59.070
even if it's vegetarian,
is generally high in fat

00:34:59.070 --> 00:35:02.310
with all the oils
and so on, and also

00:35:02.310 --> 00:35:04.710
generally high in ghee and
butter and things like that,

00:35:04.710 --> 00:35:06.572
and saturated fat and so on.

00:35:06.572 --> 00:35:08.280
So there's a lot of
room for improvement.

00:35:08.280 --> 00:35:11.130
And for whatever reason,
people of Indian descent

00:35:11.130 --> 00:35:13.410
are usually more
predisposed particularly

00:35:13.410 --> 00:35:15.490
to type II diabetes, and
often to heart disease.

00:35:15.490 --> 00:35:17.832
So these lifestyle changes
are even more important.

00:35:17.832 --> 00:35:19.290
And unfortunately,
what's happening

00:35:19.290 --> 00:35:20.730
in India is happening
in China, is

00:35:20.730 --> 00:35:22.896
happening in most of
the developing world--

00:35:22.896 --> 00:35:25.270
is that they're starting to
eat like us and live like us,

00:35:25.270 --> 00:35:27.340
and all too often die like us.

00:35:27.340 --> 00:35:29.910
And 50 or 60 years ago,
heart disease and diabetes

00:35:29.910 --> 00:35:32.490
were really pretty rare
in India and in China.

00:35:32.490 --> 00:35:35.550
And now they're by far the
number one causes of death.

00:35:35.550 --> 00:35:37.740
And it's diverting a lot
of precious resources

00:35:37.740 --> 00:35:40.150
from things that really do
require drugs, like AIDS, TB,

00:35:40.150 --> 00:35:40.692
and malaria--

00:35:40.692 --> 00:35:43.150
the things that can be largely
prevented, or even reversed,

00:35:43.150 --> 00:35:44.340
by changing lifestyle.

00:35:44.340 --> 00:35:48.624
So copy our successes,
but not our mistakes.

00:35:48.624 --> 00:35:49.290
