00:37:02.500 --> 00:37:05.166
And I knew that if I told him
he couldn't have certain foods,

00:37:05.166 --> 00:37:05.790
he'd want them.

00:37:05.790 --> 00:37:07.664
And he'd probably develop
an eating disorder.

00:37:07.664 --> 00:37:11.739
So I said, look, the rule in our
family is nobody can tell you

00:37:11.739 --> 00:37:13.530
what to eat, not even
me, and I'm your dad,

00:37:13.530 --> 00:37:15.240
and I know more about
food than a lot of people,

00:37:15.240 --> 00:37:16.350
because it's your body.

00:37:16.350 --> 00:37:18.030
You control it.

00:37:18.030 --> 00:37:19.340
This is why we eat what we eat.

00:37:19.340 --> 00:37:20.924
But you decide what
you want to have.

00:37:20.924 --> 00:37:22.590
And so we taught him
how to read labels.

00:37:22.590 --> 00:37:24.870
So he'd go into a store and say,
oh, that has too much of this.

00:37:24.870 --> 00:37:26.370
Or I don't think I
should have that.

00:37:26.370 --> 00:37:28.680
Now that all shifted when
he went through puberty.

00:37:28.680 --> 00:37:31.380
But I think that the idea
of empowering your kids

00:37:31.380 --> 00:37:33.330
and teaching them
and if you can help

00:37:33.330 --> 00:37:35.490
them grow food and actually
see where it comes from

00:37:35.490 --> 00:37:37.656
or visit a farm if you don't
want to do it yourself,

00:37:37.656 --> 00:37:38.940
it's magic to them.

00:37:38.940 --> 00:37:39.930
And they get their
taste when they're

00:37:39.930 --> 00:37:41.304
younger, their
taste preferences,

00:37:41.304 --> 00:37:42.540
which are really malleable.

00:37:42.540 --> 00:37:44.250
So if you tend to
feed them healthy food

00:37:44.250 --> 00:37:46.350
from the beginning, they
begin to actually prefer

00:37:46.350 --> 00:37:47.640
those kinds of foods.

00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:50.590
