00:38:58.920 --> 00:39:00.255
JACK: Stronger immunity, yeah.

00:39:00.255 --> 00:39:02.120
DEAN ORNISH: Well, one of the
most powerful things you can do

00:39:02.120 --> 00:39:04.290
is to actually have more love
in your life, believe it or not.

00:39:04.290 --> 00:39:06.800
There was a study that was
done by Sheldon Cohen that

00:39:06.800 --> 00:39:08.660
was in the "Journal of the
American Medical Association."

00:39:08.660 --> 00:39:11.076
And I don't know how he got
this through the Institutional

00:39:11.076 --> 00:39:12.860
Review Board, but
he got volunteers.

00:39:12.860 --> 00:39:18.320
And he dripped rhinovirus that
causes colds in their noses.

00:39:18.320 --> 00:39:20.000
100% of them got infected.

00:39:20.000 --> 00:39:22.670
But not everybody that got
infected actually got sick.

00:39:22.670 --> 00:39:25.270
And they found that the
more social contacts

00:39:25.270 --> 00:39:27.020
they had-- the more
friends visiting them,

00:39:27.020 --> 00:39:28.478
the more phone
calls, the more love

00:39:28.478 --> 00:39:30.862
that they had-- they had
four times fewer signs

00:39:30.862 --> 00:39:33.320
and symptoms of a cold, even
though they were all infected.

00:39:33.320 --> 00:39:37.070
So [INAUDIBLE] is we have
this idea that the bacteria

00:39:37.070 --> 00:39:39.590
or the germ causes the disease.

00:39:39.590 --> 00:39:41.780
But it's a necessary but
not always sufficient

00:39:41.780 --> 00:39:43.425
factor, even with
people who are--

00:39:43.425 --> 00:39:46.790
Margaret Chesney did a study at
UCSF where she found that men

00:39:46.790 --> 00:39:51.170
and women who were HIV-positive
who were lonely and depressed

00:39:51.170 --> 00:39:53.760
were more than twice as likely
to develop AIDS and die from it

00:39:53.760 --> 00:39:54.980
than those who weren't.

00:39:54.980 --> 00:39:56.224
So diet is important.

00:39:56.224 --> 00:39:57.140
Exercise is important.

00:39:57.140 --> 00:39:59.140
These all affect our
immunity, but probably more

00:39:59.140 --> 00:40:00.641
than anything, these
social factors.

00:40:00.641 --> 00:40:03.140
And we tend to think that the
time we spend with our friends

00:40:03.140 --> 00:40:05.030
and family is a luxury
that we do after we've

00:40:05.030 --> 00:40:06.332
done the important stuff.

00:40:06.332 --> 00:40:07.790
And to me, the
value of the science

00:40:07.790 --> 00:40:09.140
is that it increases awareness.

00:40:09.140 --> 00:40:12.080
So we understand just how
powerful those things are,

00:40:12.080 --> 00:40:14.651
and that the time that we spend
with our friends and family

00:40:14.651 --> 00:40:17.150
is not the stuff we do after
we've done the important stuff,

00:40:17.150 --> 00:40:18.650
that it is the important stuff.

00:40:18.650 --> 00:40:20.566
JACK: And that's also a
message for employers.

00:40:20.566 --> 00:40:23.810
I mean, obviously, here we
